content:
In CRM Analytics, Data Prep provides transformations that allow you to prepare, clean, and transform your data. 

You can use a transformation to create a calculated column based on a formula. You add transformations inside a Transform node. You can string together multiple transformations to manipulate data sequentially.

To categorize date column values into buckets:

1. In the Transform node of a Data Prep recipe, select the date column in the Preview tab.
2. Click the Bucket button to define the buckets.
3. Select whether to use absolute or relative dates.
4. Enter a label for the first bucket and specify its date range.
5. Add more buckets with later date ranges as needed.
6. Under Show Results In, select whether to create a new column or modify the original one.
7. Click Apply to add the transformation.

After running the recipe, view the bucket assigned to each row in the bucket column.
title: Categorize Date Values into Buckets in CRM Analytics
